Emergency powers and the security state were turned inward. Vice President JD Vance said on national television that Trump was considering invoking the Insurrection Act to deploy National Guard troops in Democratic\uc0\u8209 led cities. The administration had already attempted to federalize Guard units in Illinois and Oregon, ostensibly in response to protests and immigration enforcement disputes. Federal courts in both states issued restraining orders blocking deployments, and appeals courts allowed troops to remain under federal control but barred their use on the streets. The administration responded by filing an emergency appeal to the Supreme Court to lift those limits. Meanwhile, Trump spoke of using the military to address crime in Democratic cities, describing them as \'93training grounds\'94 for operations, in open defiance of the Posse Comitatus Act\'92s spirit. The language of war crept into domestic life.\
